Xinhua Review: Making Outstanding Returning Migrant Workers a Fresh Force for Rural Revitalization - Xinhua
Talent is the key to the revitalization of the countryside.
Where do you find talent?
The outstanding group of returning migrant workers is an indispensable fresh force.
Xinhua News Agency issued Shang hai Chun Zuo
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26, by wire: Make outstanding returning migrant workers a fresh force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiongjia, 34, is in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing, which earned tens of thousands of dollars a month, and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a grape growing family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, making him a little famous leader in becoming rich. He has also been selected to enter the village "two committees" team.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit farmers, such as the national fight against poverty and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a populous province and a major labor export province in the western part of China, has implemented the "Outstanding Migrant Workers Return and Training Project" in light of the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries will be produced from among the outstanding migrant workers returned, 61,000 village reserve forces will be nurtured and more than 20,000 Party members will be developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
If a well-off society is not a well-off society, the key depends on the townsfolk.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural areas of China have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the emergence of "hollowing out" in rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of grass-roots organizations in rural areas. Both the secretaries of village party branches and the ranks of party members have shown the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, aging and academic qualifications are low, and the team of leaders of village party organizations is not strong and the problems of green and yellow are prominent.
If rural talents and other elements have been flowing to the city in one direction, and the countryside has been in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
Attract back migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometown, guide them to return home and start businesses to become leaders in becoming rich, train them to become Party members and village cadres on the basis of merit, and enrich the ranks of cadres at the grass-roots level. This is a solution to the root causes of the shortage of rural Party members and grass-roots Party organizations.
Outstanding migrant workers can be brought back, and they should be allowed to stay and do a good job.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by focusing on the Party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted return, service guarantee, training and enhancement, selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, have security in their work and have hope in their lives. They can truly take root in the countryside and have a sense of achievement in starting their own businesses.
This year is the closing year of the decisive battle against poverty. Talent is the key factor in making a good connection between the fight against poverty and the revitalization of the countryside.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers and, through comprehensive measures, establish them as a task force and fresh force that can stay, fight and take them away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty eradication and well-off and development and revitalization.
