Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve to attract more than 500 species of wildlife cities to "settle" -- ScienceDaily
2020-07-26 05: 03: 17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sisuo Responsible Editor: Wang Sisuo
The natural ecology of the capital continues to improve to attract wildlife cities to "settle".
There are more than 500 species of wild animals in Beijing.
This newspaper (reporter Wang Bin) A reporter from Beijing Youth Daily learned from the Municipal Landscape and Greening Bureau that as the natural ecological environment of the capital has continued to improve in recent years, the species and number of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial spinal wild animals inhabiting Beijing has increased to more than 500, including state-level protected animals such as brown horse chicken and black stork, as well as state-level protected animals such as wildebeest, swan, gray crane and mandarin duck.
Whether it is planted into urban forests everywhere within the Second Ring or small and micro wetlands embedded between buildings, it not only brings the wild interest of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wild animals to "settle" in the city.
In the height of summer, the Songshan National Nature Reserve, located in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District, is vibrant.
A young man played leisurely by the mountain stream, while two dogs and badgers fought with each other.
In retrospect, a wild boar could not help but "scratch" on his body and was rubbing hard against the bark of the tree. Hu Qiaoli, director of the Matsuyama National Nature Reserve Administration, said that by the end of 2019, there were 178 species of wild animals, including golden eagles, state-level protected animals, spoon chickens and wildebeest, living in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares. Nearly one third of the wildlife species in the city can be seen here.
"In Matsuyama, wild animals are the true 'owners', and our staff can only be regarded as the 'bodyguards' of others at best."
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the wildlife situation in the reserve on the ground, more than 30 professional rangers inspect 16 carefully formulated protection routes every day. There will also be a "big circle" every month, spending a whole day traveling almost all over the reserve.
"During the inspection, it is necessary not only to check and record the biodiversity, but also to check the installation of artificial nests, rescue injured wild animals, install infrared cameras in the field and so on."
More than 200 infrared cameras have been installed in the Songshan National Nature Reserve to record the living conditions of wildlife in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli said that with the continuous enrichment of biodiversity in protected areas in recent years, more and more wild animals have appeared in the camera. Leopard cats, roebuck and pig badgers have become "resident guests", and the "mirror rate" of wildebeest, a second-class national protected animal, has become higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, Director of Wildlife and Wetland Protection of the Beijing Landscape and Greening Bureau, said that the number of terrestrial spinal wildlife in Beijing has increased from 461 in 1994 to more than 500 now. The species and number of wildlife in Beijing have continued to increase in recent years.
The figure of wild animals in cities is becoming more and more common, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of urban greening in the capital in recent years.
In particular, a new round of million-acre afforestation construction, which began in 2018, proposed to reshape the urban ecological environment, enhance the ecological function of woodland green space and highlight the concept of "near nature".
In the planning, we strive to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green areas, so as to facilitate wild animals to "visit relatives and friends". The trees planted are also popular honey and food source plants for animals.
Black land "planted" agricultural modernization - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26, by wire: Black land "planted" agricultural modernization
In the height of summer, two pharmaceutical spraying aircraft skimmed the 10,000-acre high-yield demonstration field at the second operation station of the Fifth Management Area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines. The words "the first field in the world" planted with black rice seedlings in the green field stood out.
Kong Lingqiang, the station manager of the operation station, said that the aircraft can spray more than 6,000 mu of arable land a day, which is about eight times more efficient than drones and hundreds of times more efficient than manual labor.
This farm is located in Friendship County, Heilongjiang Province, the largest grain producing province in China. From the sound of "Shua Shua" rice cutting in the past to the sound of "rumble" today, traditional Chinese farming and farms have achieved metamorphosis in this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve precise fertilization, reduce agricultural inputs and reduce pollution. On the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the level of standardized operation of agricultural machinery in the field.
In the process of rice production this year, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the utilization of sunlight and cultivated land resources, and can also save 16 yuan per acre in labor costs.
Farms have tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligentization in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, at present, the total number of agricultural machinery on farms is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the field has reached 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operations achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision sowing in dry fields and 100% high-powered locomotive operations in dry fields.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture and digital agriculture are the exploration direction of agricultural modernization."
Liu Hualian, director of Friendship Farm, said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large agricultural "aircraft carriers" in recent years, and has initially established a modern agricultural industry system dominated by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is an agricultural machinery Expo Park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
More than 140 agricultural machinery and equipment introduced and used by Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation over the years are on display here.
These agricultural machinery, equipment and farms have witnessed the development of agricultural modernization in China.
Give up your small family for everyone - The transfer of people of all ethnic groups in the Jiangkou River Union in Hefei, Anhui Province - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Hefei, July 26, by wire: Xie Xiaojia for everyone - the transfer of people of all ethnic groups in the Jiangkou River Union in Hefei, Anhui Province
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu, Liu Xia Cun
On July 25, at about 4 p.m., Fu Kunbao, wearing muddy rubber shoes, went from the front house to the back room and went back and forth with his wife, Zhou Yan, busy packing up his things.
"When I received a phone call from village cadres to transfer, I was still cutting grass in the field."
Fu Kunbao said that he has transferred more than 60 acres of land and grown rice, which is now growing well. "He also took medicine yesterday, and his tools and everything have not been cleaned up."
Fu Kunbao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner. "No one wants their home to be flooded. Give up their small home for everyone."
In order to cope with the persistent high water level pressure and possible heavy rainfall in Chaohu Lake, the city of Hefei, Anhui Province, is ready to open the flood diversion storage of Jiangkou River Union County, where Fu Kunbaojia is located, on the 26th.
Jiangkou River Union County is located in Feixi County, next to the Chaohu levee.
There are thousands of villagers involved in Yan Dian Township and Sanhe Township who need to be transferred.
As of 1600 hours on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, the fifth largest freshwater lake in China, remained at a high of 13.2 meters, exceeding the guaranteed water level by 0.7 meters.
The kitchen of Fu Kunbao's house is clean, with a pot of pumpkin head vegetables on the table, as well as eggs and some brine vegetables in the fridge.
"I didn't expect to move. The water of the Chiangkou River is looking good at present."
Zhou Yan said that the home is a bungalow, and some large objects have not yet thought where to put them for the time being.
"Pack up the valuable items first. Refrigerators and televisions can be put in the homes of neighbors or relatives on high ground for the time being."
Wang Li, a village cadre, gave Fu Kunbao advice.
Wang Lizheng is responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, with one household notified to confirm the resettlement plan of each person.
The closest settlement to Fu Kunbao's family is Su Xiaoxue, Yan Dian Township, about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to large pieces, Fu Kunbao and his wife also have a headache with more than 1,000 jin of grain and some newly bought furniture in their home.
"The grain is ready to be dragged to relatives' homes. There is no way to move the furniture."
As soon as the couple discussed, they put a stool under the newly bought bed and raised the bed by about half a meter.
At 6 p.m., Fu Kunbao began to use a tricycle to transport things to relatives' homes, and Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
At about 11 p.m., the couple looked at it before and after at home, pulled the electric gate and prepared to go to the settlement.
"I hope the water will return early."
Fu Kunbao said.
On July 26, at 9: 30 a.m., the reporter saw at the scene of Jiangkou River Union County that the local area had made all preparations before flood diversion.
