Church fire in Nantes, France: Parish volunteers admit to arson and are usually kind and taciturn - CNN
On July 26, according to foreign media, on July 18, the famous Cathedral of St. Peter and St. Paul, a gem of religious and historical buildings in Nantes, France, was severely damaged in a fire, and the large organ was completely destroyed.
On the 26th local time, the Nantes prosecutor announced that a parish volunteer in charge of security in the cathedral had been charged with "arson and destruction".
He has admitted that he set the fire in the church.
According to the report, local prosecutor Senas said that the 39-year-old parish volunteer from Rwanda admitted that he set fire to three of the cathedrals at night.
The lawyer of the man said that the arsonist now regrets doing such a thing.
This man entered France a few years ago through the means of asylum. He was sheltered in the parish where the fire occurred and taken in in the church.
The prosecution pointed out that recently, he tried to renew his visa and was in dialogue and communication with the police station on this issue.
However, the church said it still could not believe that the usually very kind, smiling, but not very talkative believer would destroy the church he loved so much.
On the day of the fire on July 18, the volunteer had already been questioned and investigated by the police because of illogical problems in his account, but he was later released.
The picture shows firefighters carrying out rescue at the scene.
On the evening of the 25th, the man was arraigned again because the professional engineers of the laboratory of the Central Police Department in Paris obtained new evidence.
This time, the man admitted to setting the fire.
It is reported that if convicted of intentional arson and destruction, the suspect may face 10 years' imprisonment and a fine of 150,000 euros.
According to the report, the fire caused serious losses to the Cathedral of St. Pierre and St. Paul. The organ in the church was completely destroyed and the colored glass windows behind the organ were also severely damaged.
According to Brunet, the chief architect of French historical conservation buildings, it is conservatively estimated that the restoration of Nantes Cathedral will take at least three years.
Comprehensive news: American unilateralism undermines bilateral relations. International public opinion supports China's countermeasure against the United States - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 26 (Xinhua) -- On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the US Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the establishment and operation license of the US Consulate General in Chengdu and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all business and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateralist measures taken by the United States have caused serious distress to the relations between China and the United States. China has responded to unreasonable provocations by the United States, and it is legitimate and necessary to take countermeasures.
Andres Borks, director of the China Research Center of the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateralist measures of the United States have damaged the bridge of understanding between the Chinese and American peoples and caused a crisis in the relations between the two great powers.
China's notification to the United States of the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures of the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Arab-China Research Center, believes that China's above decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocations of the United States and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The United States is trying to divert the attention of the American people by pressuring China to cover up its poor response to the new crown epidemic.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the United States has adopted a provocative diplomatic posture, which has caused serious distress to the relations between China and the United States, which are facing serious challenges.
China's notification to the United States of the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure, in line with diplomatic practice, and not only reflects China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the rational and beneficial nature of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's above decision is a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
In order for China-US relations to return to normal, the United States should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve win-win economic and political results with China and how to benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Youssef, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab Indigenous China Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures China is forced to take are a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, in line with international law and the basic norms of international relations, as well as in line with diplomatic practices.
Previously, the United States requested the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston in serious violation of international law and the basic norms of international relations.
It is hoped that the United States will revoke the previous relevant decisions and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's Lianhe Zaobao newspaper published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to encircle China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the pressure of the United States, although China is very reluctant to see China-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
