Jiangxi opens up a "green channel" for young people on the front line of flood control to enlist in the army - Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Nanchang, July 26 (Guo Dongming, Xiong Liang) The conscription office of the Jiangxi Provincial People's Government recently made it clear that priority shall be given to individuals or their children who have performed outstanding in this flood rescue and relief mission who meet the conditions for recruitment and have passed both medical examination and political examination.
"After the registration of young conscripts, we will give priority to the appointment of soldiers after verification by the community where the young conscripts are located, the Street Armed Forces Department and the Shuyang District Conscription Office."
Wang Hui, Vice Minister of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces of Shuyang District of Jiujiang City, said that affected by the flood, they concentrated on three days to organize medical examinations for young candidates starting on the 25th.
Zhou Jingfan, a young conscript in Shuyang District of Jiujiang City, is a 22-year-old college graduate. His mother is a community worker and his father is a veteran of a department of the Air Force. Zhou Jingfan's parents have been on duty on the flood control and flood fighting line for ten days.
"These days, I see in the news that the people's children and soldiers are desperate to defend their hometown on the flood line. I also want to be like them."
Zhou Jingfan said that he had a dream of joining the army since he was a child, and through this flood fight, he strengthened his determination to join the military camp.
Jiujiang City also regards flood rescue as a "living textbook" for conscription propaganda. Taking the community as the unit, they call on young conscripts to voluntarily participate in the tasks of patrolling and checking embankments and guarding on duty. They now understand the nature and purpose of the people's army and strengthen their confidence in joining the army and reporting to the country.
Luo Jiuyu, commissar of the Ministry of People's Armed Forces of Shuyang District of Jiujiang City, said that by giving priority to the appointment of soldiers, he hoped to inspire more young conscripts and create a good social atmosphere to participate in the task with honor and join the army with honor.
