"The South of the Yangtze River" Pursues the Poetic "Dream of the Yellow River" -- ScienceDaily
(China's Poverty Alleviation Story) "The South of the Yangtze River" Pursues the Poetic "Dream of the Yellow River"
Yinchuan, China News Agency, July 26 (Yang Di) "The Jiuqu Yellow River is thousands of miles of sand, and the waves are from the horizon."
The Yellow River, which aroused the pride of countless literati Akako wanzhang, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Today, Ningxia, which has the nickname of "plugging the south of the Yangtze River", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
The "Bibo Dream" of River Qingshui Show
"The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia", and the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, making it the "mother river" for raising one side.
However, with the rapid progress of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization and management and protection of rivers and lakes are unbalanced, and disturbances such as excessive sewage discharge, land construction around lakes and encroachment on waters have come to the fore, leading to black odor of water bodies, excessive water quality, messy environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of water ecological diversity and striving to return the Yellow River to Xiuhe Qing.
Water control should be carried out from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local area has adopted the method of "raising standards + controlling pollution + strictly controlling". All sewage in industrial parks has been centrally treated, all urban sewage treatment plants have achieved first-class A standard discharge, and black and smelly water bodies in urban built-up areas have been basically eliminated. The third batch of Chinese black and smelly water demonstration cities have been successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake long system in 2017. Today, it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake long responsibility system in districts, cities and counties, and river and lake long patrol has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, lives in a village along the Yellow River. He has witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: "The former water has a stench, and the stench is gone after remediation."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is good and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Sha Ji Xiangji
Flying birds, green trees, trestles, blue water... The beautiful scenery of Fan Zhongyan's "sand and sand collection" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, and a variety of wetlands, including river wetlands, lake wetlands and marsh wetlands, have been formed along the way, which play an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and water ecological balance. At the same time, it has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, the relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of about RMB3.45 billion in wetland protection projects. At present, the Yinchuan wetland area is 192,000 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and marsh wetlands. There are five national wetland parks, one national urban wetland park, six autonomous region level wetland parks and eight municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Conservation Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. "The remaining gull is an endangered bird, with only more than 20,000 in the world, of which Yinchuan Wetland is home to more than 2,000."
At the same time, Ningxia has drawn a red line with a 500-meter range for the wetland protection areas on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the treatment of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of the nine main yellow drains in Ningxia has now reached 100% of the Class IV standard. "Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming and the flowers are blooming."
The "Drinking Dream" of Pu Huimin Sheng
Yinchuan City, Ningxia, once had an "awkward" title: The only city along the Yellow River to "keep the Yellow River short of water and drink".
Since 2010, Yinchuan has been facing the problem of water shortage at the peak of the summer period. The "pain of water shortage" in the past decade has become a painful summer experience for many high-floor residents. However, under the current situation that major water sources are at the limit of overexploitation and large areas of groundwater overexploitation funnel areas have been formed underground in urban areas, water shortage has become a difficult problem for Yinchuan.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking the purified Yellow River has become a good solution to the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Municipal Water Bureau, said that in order to improve the water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan for domestic production, Ningxia duly launched the water supply project on the urban and rural western route of Yinchuan Metropolitan Area, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project was officially opened to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will take into account the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply in an integrated manner. "In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered rural water supply points into the Western Route water supply project. It is expected that the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan region will be basically realized by the end of this year."
