The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has a "temperature" -- ScienceDaily
2020-07-26 07: 01: 37 Source: Economic Daily Author: Wang Sisuo Responsible Editor: Wang Sisuo
The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has a "temperature".
Economic Daily China Economic Network reporter Lin Huocan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the Xincrown Pneumonia epidemic, China has promoted the prevention and control of the epidemic and economic and social development in an integrated manner. The situation of the prevention and control of the epidemic has continued to improve, the steady recovery of the economy has been obvious, and the performance of employment and prices, which are closely related to the people's livelihood, has been generally stable. The Chinese economy has handed over a report card on the operation of the economy with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the survey unemployment rate rose.
In particular, in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of shutdown, the employment demand of enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the urban survey unemployment rate rose.
With the gradual improvement of the situation of epidemic prevention and control, the production and living order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Central Committee of the Party adheres to the general tone of the work of steady progress, further strengthens the hedging of macro-policies, comprehensively strengthens employment priority policies, and actively promotes the work of helping to stabilize and expand employment.
China has increased its policies to hedge and stabilize jobs, played a combination of "relief and slow return compensation" policies, reduced and reduced the contributions of three social insurance units in a phased manner, allowed the postponement of the payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of the stable return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises, and provided absorption subsidies and trainee subsidies to enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various stable employment policies, the employment demand of enterprises has steadily picked up, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the urban survey unemployment rate has gradually declined. In June, the survey unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, Director of the Population and Employment Statistics Department of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to bear fruit, and the labor force that withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic in the early period returned in succession. The urban labor force participation rate rose by about 10 percentage points in June compared with February, close to the level of the same period last year.
The data showed that the total amount of urban employment increased by more than 19% in June compared with February, and most industries reached pre-epidemic levels. The average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February and slightly 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose 5.4% year-on-year, a multi-year high.
Entering February, the year-on-year increase in CPI fell slightly, but it was still in the "5 range".
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, driven by consumer demand before the Spring Festival, as well as the wrong month of the Spring Festival and the low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, all parts of the country experienced logistics delays, untimely supply of materials and increased transportation costs of materials in January and February. Together with the hoarding and rush of some citizens, the prices of some basic necessities rose significantly.
In order to deal with the disturbance caused by the prevention and control of the epidemic to the price situation, the relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation security to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the role of a series of policy measures, the supply of vegetables, melons and fruits in the market has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government issued the policy of ensuring supply and stable prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it. The supply of pork reserves has improved markedly, pig production capacity has been restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and marketing has gradually become normal.
Since March, pork prices have fallen continuously, driving the year-on-year increase in food prices to fall back to 10.6% in May. In June, pork prices rose slightly year-on-year due to factors such as the slowdown in hog production, the decrease in imports and the recovery of group consumer demand.
The seasonal changes in the price of fresh vegetables are obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Influenced by the high comparative base in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruit continued to decline year-on-year, falling by an average of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation logistics, various regions have increased their efforts to guarantee supply, and the supply and demand situation in the market has improved.
Since March, the CPI has fallen year-on-year for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June. The price level has generally returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to remain moderate, and the overall inflationary pressure is small, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order on the premise of doing a good job in normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
We will effectively deal with natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major agricultural producing areas such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on hoarding and price gouging that disrupt market order.
