This series of measures quickly achieved positive results. By mid-May, the new confirmed cases of newly crowned pneumonia in Israel fell back to single digits in a single day.
With the control of the epidemic, all prevention and control measures in Israel have been fully unsealed. Since June, the number of new diagnoses of Xincrown Pneumonia has gradually rebounded.
In particular, after entering July, the spread of the epidemic has been accelerating.
In recent days, there have been more than 1,500 new cases in Israel per day for eight days. As of the time of writing on July 25, there were 916 new cases on the same day.
As of July 25, there were 59,745 confirmed cases and 448 deaths in Israel.
