The Lancet article praised China's anti-epidemic efforts to encourage all countries to learn from their experiences -- ScienceDaily
According to an article published in The Lancet magazine on the 25th, China, as a country with a population of 1.4 billion and similar in size to Europe or the United States, has effectively controlled the new crown epidemic at this stage, without widespread transmission, and has largely controlled the domestic epidemic.
The article said that in the past decade or so, China has made a lot of investment in domestic research and public health construction, which makes China's preparation for the new crown much more adequate than that of Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) that year.
The authors said that when SARS broke out in 2002, China was ill-prepared at first, especially the pathogen could not be determined.
When the new crown virus was discovered in December 2019, Chinese scientists were soon able to identify the virus species and shared genome sequencing data with the international community on January 11, 2020.
By the end of January, doctors from mainland China and Hong Kong had clarified the clinical characteristics of the virus and warned the world of the threat of the new crown virus through research papers published in The Lancet.
China has also been at the forefront of vaccine research. Under the declaration of a state of emergency, through close cooperation at home, such research has been carried out very quickly and rigorously. In May and July, the results of the progress made in the early trial of the new crown vaccine developed by China were published in The Lancet, respectively.
China's experience shows that it is very important to invest in the national health and research system and effectively improve laboratory capacity.
This is the basis for the country to respond quickly and effectively to health emergencies and global health security.
For other countries, especially low-income and middle-income countries, it is well worth learning from and learning from.
In addition, China's experience has proved that on the basis of strong research, it is necessary to have a strong senior level to make correct decisions decisively on the basis of scientific basis, so that the new crown epidemic can be effectively controlled.
The article stressed that the government and its leaders must respect science, understand the value of science and take action against it in a way that is most beneficial to society.
In the early days of the outbreak, the National Health and Construction Commission of China sent three groups of infectious disease experts to Wuhan to investigate the risk and spread of the new crown virus. Their suggestions provided a basis for the decision to "seal the city" in Wuhan on January 23. When experts raised the necessity and urgency of building a square cabin hospital, the government quickly made a decision and implemented it quickly. At the same time, the broad participation of the community and the masses also enabled the epidemic to be controlled quickly and effectively.
At the end of the article, it is stressed that in response to global health emergencies, all countries need to strengthen global cooperation and jointly respond to them.
