On July 26, according to the website of the Supreme Inspection, in the first half of this year, procuratorial organs across the country prosecuted a total of 5,8101 people for fraud crimes, an increase of 35% year-on-year.
In particular, among the crimes against the prevention and control of the epidemic, fraud crimes are frequent, and the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by procuratorial organs accounts for 43.4% of the total number of crimes against the prevention and control of the epidemic.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance. Of the ten batches of typical cases involving epidemic prevention and control that have been issued at present, a total of 9 have involved the crime of fraud.
From the handling of cases by the procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are a wide variety of fraud crimes involved, ranging from the national macro policy to the food, clothing and housing of the common people, including epidemic fraud, "medical care" fraud, "health products" fraud, "enrollment intermediary" fraud, "routine loan" fraud, fraudulent state subsidy fraud, national asset thawing fraud, and so on. They continue to "innovate", covering education, medical care, employment, old age, social security, land requisition and demolition, precise poverty alleviation, financial credit and other areas, which not only cause economic losses to the victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecom network frauds break through the restrictions of national borders, regions and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholders, cross-border, remote and electronic payment. There are many unspecified victims, which is very harmful.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or posts, use legitimate online platforms to publicize and recruit, train and evaluate recruiters, adopt enterprise operation model management, wear a "legal cloak" and are more beguiling.
It is incumbent upon the procuratorial organs to punish and prevent crimes in accordance with the law and issue early warnings to the public and relevant departments in a timely manner.
