Understand what professional grade difference is before volunteering to fill in - CNN
2020-07-27 02: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Responsible Editor: Yu Xiao
Understand what professional grade difference is before volunteering to fill in
Every year, when they volunteer for the college entrance examination, some students or parents do not understand the nouns involved in the voluntary filing, which in turn affects the voluntary filing.
This year, five universities, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology, jointly issued enrollment policies for 2020, eliminating professional grade differences.
What does professional grade difference mean and what is the significance in voluntary filing?
There are three rules for the allocation of specialties.
Experts reminded that before filling in the volunteer, it is important to read the Admissions Charter of the desired school in detail and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of transfers and the rules for the allocation of specialties.
The rules for the allocation of specialties mean that after the transfer of colleges and universities, there are three main ways for professional admission: Professional priority, grade priority and professional grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be made clear in the Admissions Charter.
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the total score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates within the scope of admission will be queued according to the total score. When the score does not reach the voluntary admission score line for the first major, it depends on whether they have reached the voluntary admission score line for the second major, and so on until they are admitted to the last professional volunteer. There is no grade difference between the volunteers for each major.
The so-called "professional grade difference" means that when arranging candidates' majors, institutions determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates in different specialties according to one or more score values published in the admission charter. This score value is the "professional grade difference".
That is, the difference between the scores of institutions when admitting candidates who volunteer for the first major and those who do not volunteer for the first major, and the grade difference between volunteers for each major, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Assuming that Xiaoming, a student, applied for the A university and scored 560 points in the examination, his professional volunteers are: Computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering and e-commerce. The professional admission of A colleges and universities is based on the method of professional grade difference, which is divided into 2, 1, 1 and 0.
If Xiaoming meets the requirements of the first major, Xiaoming will be admitted to the "computer" major when the major meets the balance of the first major admission plan. If the computer is not accepted, his score will be subtracted by two points, and the score will be ranked with that of the candidates who volunteered for the "international trade" examination in the first major to determine whether he meets the professional admission conditions. If he still cannot be met, the score will be subtracted by one point (i.e. 557 points) for the voluntary "automation" of the third major. If he still cannot be satisfied, the score will be subtracted by one point (i.e. 556 points) for the admission of the fourth major. If the subsequent major still cannot meet his professional volunteer, the score will not be reduced, and so on.
The professional grade difference setting of different universities is different.
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now eliminated professional grade differences, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. From the Admissions Charter published by each university, more than 20 universities have set up professional grade differences this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Institute, etc.
In these colleges and universities, the professional grade difference set up by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences in each major. For example, Ningxia University. Candidates whose files have been submitted to the university will be admitted in order of scores after decreasing by one point according to the order in which candidates fill in their professional volunteers.
And some universities have set up different professional grade differences between different specialties.
For example, at Jimei University, the total professional volunteer grade difference is 4 points, that is, the grade difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points. There is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers. The professional grade difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When volunteering, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is any professional grade difference and what is the form of the grade difference. While taking full account of the score, they should also rationally analyze the proposed school and major. If the institution explicitly adopts the grade difference method for admission in the admission charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the specialties and improve the admission odds when choosing the major.
